 The arrest came after members of the Crime Intelligence Unit in Witbank received information of a truck carrying sugar from Malelane to Johannesburg was transporting dagga.  The members, together with the Middelburg Flying Squad, stopped and searched the truck.
Bags of compressed marijuana to the estimated street value of R370 000 were found. The suspects were arrested and will appear in the Witbank Magistrate’s Court today on charges of dealing in dagga.      Four killed after minibus and truck collide on N11 near Doornkop Elderly lady escapes with her life Parkrun fever breaks out Military troop imposter arrested • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za